        <div class="rules-box">
          <h2 class="text-center"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Library Rules & Regulations</h2>
          <div class="row">
              <div class="col-md-6">
                  <ol>
                      <li><strong>Respect Quiet Zones</strong>
                          <p>Maintain silence in designated quiet areas to ensure a conducive study environment for everyone.</p>
                      </li>
                      <li><strong>No Food or Drinks</strong>
                          <p>Only water in closed containers is allowed. Avoid bringing food or other beverages to protect library materials and equipment.</p>
                      </li>
                      <li><strong>Handle Materials with Care</strong>
                          <p>Treat books, journals, and other resources with respect. Do not write, tear, or damage any library property.</p>
                      </li>
                      <li><strong>Return Books on Time</strong>
                          <p>Borrowed items must be returned by the due date. Late returns may result in fines or suspension of borrowing privileges.</p>
                      </li>
                  </ol>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-6">
                  <ol start="5">
                      <li><strong>Use Electronic Devices Responsibly</strong>
                          <p>Set phones to silent mode and take calls outside the library. Use headphones for audio and keep the volume low.</p>
                      </li>
                      <li><strong>Follow Computer and Internet Policies</strong>
                          <p>Use library computers for academic purposes only. Do not access inappropriate content or violate copyright laws.</p>
                      </li>
                      <li><strong>No Unauthorized Removal of Materials</strong>
                          <p>Do not take books, journals, or other resources out of the library without checking them out properly.</p>
                      </li>
                      <li><strong>Report Issues to Staff</strong>
                          <p>If you encounter any problems (e.g., damaged books, noise disturbances), inform library staff immediately.</p>
                      </li>
                  </ol>
              </div>
